<br>
::With that Hades bowed slightly at the waist, of course not taking his eyes off of her::<br>
<br>
&quot;I am Hades; Lord of Underworld, King of the Dead, Master of Tartarus. Mortals do tremble when they hear my name, and fear to speak it aloud, for fear of me hearing it and attracting my attention.&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=celticmorrigan>Celtic Morrigan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Lady of the Lake</span><br>  Posts: 23<br> <font color=#993300>(4/25/03 5:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm65.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/thephantomqueen/images/morrigan26.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Introduction</span><hr size=1> Her head cocked to the side as he scanned her, she raised a brow slightly. She had felt his relationship to death as well, figuring him to be a god of it.<br>
